# MXR Phase 45 PCB Project

## Background

This project was part of a university electronics assignment.  
The goal was to design and build any type of electronic project, and I chose to create a phaser guitar pedal.

The circuit is based on the classic MXR Phase 45 design.

## Objectives

- Design a working PCB using KiCad
- Route through-hole components
- Generate Gerber files for PCB fabrication

## Design Process

The schematic was recreated based on available circuit diagrams.

The PCB was then designed using KiCad 9. Component placement was adjusted to keep signal paths relatively short and to make the board easy to assemble.

## Challenges

Some issues encountered during the design process included:

- routing constraints due to through-hole components
- LED footprint selection
- switching noise when engaging the bypass

### Future revisions

- change the LED from SMT to THT
- add noise filtering when in bypass mode

